First Lady Melania Trump has appointed Lindsay Reynolds as Assistant to the President and Chief of Staff to the First Lady. Reynolds will be responsible for managing the agenda and day to day operations of the Office of the First Lady. Reynolds brings over fourteen years of experience in political fundraising, event management, and logistical expertise. She previously served in the White House under President George W. Bush. Melania Trump expressed her excitement in putting together a professional and highly-experienced team, while Reynolds stated that she looks forward to serving as the First Lady's Chief of Staff and supporting President Trump. Reynolds also mentioned that she is working to ensure that the White House Visitors Office is fully staffed and operational, and that routine maintenance, updates, and renovations are being done along the tour route to enhance the guest experience.